genresAdvancedInfo.name: chechen pop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A genre of pop music that originated in the Chechen Republic of Russia. Chechen pop is known for its catchy melodies, upbeat rhythms, and emotionally charged lyrics. The music often features traditional Chechen instruments, such as the dombra and the accordion, as well as modern electronic elements. Chechen pop has become increasingly popular in recent years, both within the region and beyond.
